			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: HP or AC?<a name="63710"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 23 04 1:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Both, some items have great ac and gimp hp, others have gimp ac and great hp. Avoid these items.  Get a balance.
<br />

<br />
When somethin is hitting you for 1k+ having an extra 50hp wont make a detectable difference to your survival. Big AC will seriously help
<br />

<br />
When something is casting unresistable AE spells for 1k dmg, that extra AC wont have the slightest effect.  The only defense you have is lots of hp's
<br />

<br />
You need both.
<br />

<br />
On raids HP &gt; AC because you shouldnt be getting hit that much, most of your dmg should be from AE's and the like.  Grouping you will get hit a lot more so AC &gt; HP.  
<br />

<br />
Theres a lot of crap talked about big hp's, most people judge a tank by his HP.  I think this is misguided.   In any guild you will regularly hear someone going on about achieving a new HP high, I do it myself.  So I think a lot of people go for HP cos they can show off.
<br />

<br />
Slowly the serious players are waking up to the value of big AC and the value of a tank with 2k+ AC is now much higher.
<br />

<br />
Also I would say that focusing on HP/AC is a mistake for a bard.  Focus on AC/HP/MANA/CHA, not necessarily in that order.  You need them all.
<br />

<br />

<br />
My 2cp
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
