				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">When somethin is hitting you for 1k+ having an extra 50hp wont make a detectable difference to your survival. Big AC will seriously help </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
That seriously holds true, and we as bards don't have that much AC or Hp to begin with, but I will say this.
<br />

<br />
With the release of GoD and OoW you better believe AC is more important than HP. In fact it cannot be even compared when you are getting hit for 2k+.
<br />

<br />
If you don't have AC and you can't reduce 1-2k (4 hit + kick/bash) of dmg. You are looking at instant death unless you have 8k hp... which then you have to survive the next round of attacks.
<br />

<br />
Spell dmg is another issues ... AC is neglected when your are getting AE. So you still need hp.
<br />

<br />
Edit: You need about 2k AC, and trust me its hard to do that as a bard.</span></td>
