				<td colspan="2"><span>Both AC and HP will come over time with gear upgrades. LDoN's is a great way to work on building up your armor, if you're either not in a guild or if your guild doesn't raid a whole lot. Even with the new expansions, Bards are in high demand for LDoN's. 
<br />

<br />
I personally went more to the AC route first, but along with that, went defensive on my AA's as well, since at the time, I was an off-tank on our guild raids. And I got some HP gear as well. Since then our guild has grown so I don't have to fill that roll much now, but when on CC duty's or just getting smacked around, there's a huge difference in the damage I take now versus a couple hundred AC ago. ATM fully 65 raid buffed, I'm at 6400HP, 1400AC. 
